<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12127d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12127d">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12127d"> 127(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> regulars teach seculars / theology</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">En 1383, il devient lecteur en th&eacute;ologie &agrave; la &ldquo;Seo&rdquo; &mdash; le Si&egrave;ge &mdash; entendre par l&agrave; la cath&eacute;drale de Valence. Ce cours de th&eacute;ologie est public. Tout la&iuml;c instruit peut l&apos;entendre, mais il s&apos;adresse surtout au clerg&eacute; s&eacute;culier. <br>[In 1383 he became reader in theology at the Seo, the Seat, meaning the cathedral at Valence. This theology course was public. Every educated layman could attend, but it was addressed mostly to the secular clergy. <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 24</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Regular: subject to a religious rule, belonging to an order (as opposed to <i>secular</i>, member of the clergy living in the world). </mm> </dd></dl>
